@startuml sequence_notification_flow
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Notification Data Flow — Load, Mark-Read, Real-Time Push

actor User
participant "HeaderComponent" as Header
participant "NotificationService" as NS
participant "REST API" as API
participant "SignalR Hub" as Hub
database "SQL Server" as DB

== App Initialization ==
User -> Header: App loads (ngOnInit)
Header -> NS: startConnection(token)
NS -> Hub: negotiate + connect
Hub --> NS: connected

== Bell Dropdown Opened ==
User -> Header: Click bell icon
Header -> NS: loadRecentNotifications()
NS -> API: GET /notifications?page=1&pageSize=20
API -> DB: SELECT TOP 20\nWHERE OrgId = @OrgId\nORDER BY CreatedAt DESC
DB --> API: notifications[]
API --> NS: { items, totalCount }
NS --> Header: notifications$.next(items)
Header --> User: Render dropdown with items

== Mark Single as Read ==
User -> Header: Click notification item
Header -> NS: markAsRead(notificationId)
NS -> API: PUT /notifications/{id}/read
API -> DB: UPDATE SET IsRead = true
DB --> API: ok
API --> NS: 200 OK
NS --> Header: Update notifications$ + unreadCount$
Header -> User: Navigate to entity route

== Mark All as Read ==
User -> Header: Click "Mark all as read"
Header -> NS: markAllAsRead()
NS -> API: PUT /notifications/mark-all-read
API -> DB: UPDATE SET IsRead = true\nWHERE UserId = @UserId AND IsRead = false
DB --> API: ok
API --> NS: 200 OK
NS --> Header: unreadCount$.next(0)
Header --> User: Badge hidden

== Real-Time Push ==
Hub -> NS: ReceiveNotification(notification)
NS --> Header: Prepend to notifications$\nIncrement unreadCount$
Header --> User: Badge count updated

@enduml
